**Class**

Class -> blueprint / template to create something -> Person

Real Objects - Instance of the class.


fields, member variables or instance variables** ->  Attributes **

member methods or instance methods -> **Behaviours**

**Class**

1. Attributes
2. Behaviour
3. _inner class_
4. _static fields methods._


Object-Oriented Programming is a **methodology or paradigm** to design a program using classes and objects.



Class is a Blueprint / user-defined data type which defines its properties(attributes) and its methods(behaviours).

